## K. `M127` with `d=phi(3^6)=486` (sparse-only sweep)

Same objective as prior sections (`n_F=2^28..2^40`, minimize `n_sis=n*d` first, then minimize overshoot above 128).

- `q = 2^127 - 1`
- `eta = 729`, `d = phi(729) = 486`
- D.7 check: `ord_eta(q)=27`, valid `z=[27]`
- Sparse ternary threshold at length 486:
  - `w_min = 19`
  - `log2(C(486,19)*2^19) ~= 131.3018`
- Sparse-aware `T`: `T_sparse_l1 = alpha*w = 2*19 = 38`

